      "text": [
        " لَا يَنْفَعُ اجْتِهَادٌ لَا وَرَعَ فِيهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Ibn Fazzal, from Abu Jameela, from Ibn Abu Yafour, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The striving would not benefit if there is no devoutness in it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn Khalid from ibn Faddal from abu Jamilah from ibn abu Ya’fur from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) has said, ‘Hard work without restraint from worldly things (sins) is of no benefit.’” "
        ]
      }
